<TITLE> Huge diesel spills out, pillage suspected </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)A huge quantity of diesel gushed out on Friday as leakages developed in a tanker of a Jamuna company depot at Sreemongal in Moulovibazar. The caretaker of the depot , Anwar Miah, told bdnews24.com about 150 litres of diesel poured out of the tanker after a burst of gate bulb because of excessive pressure of oil. The tanker had a reserve of about eight lakh litres of diesel, he said The gush of oil stopped after the gate bulb had been repaired, the security officials said. Sreemongal police chief Enamul Monwar told bdnews24.com that on information from the locals around 12:30pm, police and fire fighters rushed to the spot. No-one associated with the depot informed the police station even after such an alarming incident, he added On reaching the spot, they found huge quantity of diesel pouring out of the tanker, which might cause a massive blaze, Abdur Rahim, sub-inspector of Sreemongal police, said. An official recently transferred to another depot told bdnews24.com on condition of anonymity that smuggling of oil took place from this depot almost every night. Some locals refusing to be named alleged that the incident occurred because of oil smuggling. The depot officials are involved in the smuggling, they also said. Monwar said they were investigating the incident after filing a general dairy. bdnews2
